  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Addressing acute Water, Sanitation and Hygiene needs of vulnerable and disaster affected population</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- 15 boreholes rehabilitationed (7 in Koch town payam and 8 in Mirmir payam)
- 35 hand pump mechanics and community water user committee members trained
- 13 toilets repaired
- 30 hygiene promoters trained
- Community and school hygiene campaigns</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1. Increase access to portable water for domestic use and drinking for 10,700 crisis affected people in Koch Town and Mirmir payams
2. Improve access to sanitation facilities and hygiene behaviour in Koch Town and Mirmir payams</narrative>
  </description>
